'''Friends of WikiLeaks''', sometimes reduced and stylized as '''FoWL''', was a surveillance-resistant [[Social networking service|social network site]] created in support of [[WikiLeaks]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lesoir-echos.com/fowl-le-%C2%AB%E2%80%89facebook-killer%E2%80%89%C2%BB/monde/45397/|title=FoWL, le " Facebook killer "|last=Girard|first=Céline |date=22 February 2012|publisher=[[Le Soir]]|language=French|accessdate=19 October 2012}}</ref> Founded in May 2012, the site was intended for those who support WikiLeaks and its activities to perform advocacy.<ref name="bgr">{{cite web|title=WikiLeaks launches encrypted social network |first= Dan|last= Graziano |date=22 May 2012|publisher=bgr.com|url=http://www.bgr.com/2012/05/22/wikileaks-supportes-launch-social-network/ | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20131204102457/http://bgr.com/2012/05/22/wikileaks-supportes-launch-social-network/ | archivedate = 2013-12-04| deadurl=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://wlfriends.org/ |title=Friends of Wikileads | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20130809164256/https://wlfriends.org/ | archivedate = 2013-08-09| deadurl=yes}} website.</ref><ref>{{cite web |title='Friends of WikiLeaks' fight for Assange's rights in European Court |date=19 June 2012 |publisher=RT.com |url=https://rt.com/news/friends-of-wikileaks-court-appeal-221/|accessdate=31 August 2012 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20130502021333/http://rt.com/news/friends-of-wikileaks-court-appeal-221/ | archivedate = 2013-05-02| deadurl=yes}}</ref> In contrast to more traditional forms of social networking, FoWL aimed at bringing together like-minded people who do not yet know each other. To achieve this goal, the site would ask about the language the user speaks as well as any preferences in the ways of hobbies or other activities. The site would then find six friends who share the user's views within your country, and another six from other parts of the world who speak your language.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.uk/articles/343872/20120522/wikileaks-launches-wlfriends-social-network.htm |title=Wikileaks v Facebook: Friends of Wikileaks Social Network Launched - IBTimes UK |publisher=Ibtimes.co.uk |date=2012-05-22 |accessdate=2012-10-28}}</ref> If one of those friends cancelled their account or became inactive, a new friend would be matched to the user's circle and would replace the previous inactive one.
{{rquote|right|"Friends of WikiLeaks is a network of people from across the globe who defend WikiLeaks, its people, its alleged sources and its mission"|Friends of WikiLeaks<ref name="bgr" />}}
With the establishment of [[The Wikileaks Party]], the official Friends of WikiLeaks organization was shut down in 2013. However, several of the groups still remain active on Twitter and the web as of 28 July 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://fowlchicago.wordpress.com/2012/12/19/friends-of-wikileaks-international-directory/|title=Friends of WikiLeaks International Directory - Updating July 2017|work=Friends of WikiLeaks - Chicago}}</ref>
