'''Our Global Neighborhood''' is the report of the [[Commission on Global Governance]],<ref>http://www.gdrc.org/u-gov/global-neighbourhood/</ref> issued in 1995, advancing the view that nations are [[interdependence|interdependent]] and calling for a strengthened [[United Nations]]. It was vigorously criticized by [[The New American]] magazine, [[John Birch Society]], and other advocates of national [[sovereignty]]. In ''Toward Genuine Global Governance: Critical Reactions to "Our Global Neighborhood"'', Harris, Errol E. and Yunker, James A. assembled a set of nine essays by [[world federalism|world federalist]]s expressing their disappointment in the report.
