{{Infobox academic | honorific_prefix = | name = Seth Kalichman | honorific_suffix = | native_name = | native_name_lang = | image = | image_size = | alt = | caption = | birth_name = <!-- Use only if different from full/othernames --> | birth_date = <!-- {{birth date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | birth_place = | death_date = <!-- {{death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date then birth date) --> | death_place = | death_cause = | region = | nationality = | period = | occupation = [[Professor]] | title = | boards = <!-- Board or similar positions extraneous to main occupation - e.g. "Editoral board of The Journal of Sociology" --> | known_for = [[Sexual Compulsivity Scale]] | spouse = | children = | signature = | signature_alt = | signature_size = | era = [[21st century]] | discipline = [[Social psychology]] | sub_discipline = [[Community psychology|Community psychologist]] | movement = <!-- Should match the idiologial movement or denomination (for religious), "school" of thought etc. (e.g. "Anglican", "Postmodernist", "Socialist" or "Green" etc. --> | religion = <!-- Religion should be supported with a citation from a reliable source --> | denomination = <!-- Religious denomination should be supported with a citation from a reliable source --> | education = | alma_mater = | thesis_title = | thesis_url = | thesis_year = | doctoral_advisor = | doctoral_students = | notable_students = | main_interests = [[HIV]]/[[AIDS]] | workplaces = [[University of Connecticut]] | notable_works = ''Denying AIDS: Conspiracy Theories, Pseudoscience, and Human Tragedy'' | notable_ideas = | influences = [[Nicoli Nattrass]] | influenced = | awards = | website = | footnotes = }}
'''Seth C. Kalichman''' is a clinical [[Community psychology|community psychologist]] and professor of [[social psychology]] at the [[University of Connecticut]], who researches [[HIV]]/[[AIDS]] prevention and care.
Kalichman is the director of the Southeast HIV/AIDS Research & Education Project in [[Atlanta, Georgia]] and [[Cape Town, South Africa]]; the editor of the journal ''[[AIDS and Behavior]]''; and the author of ''Denying AIDS: Conspiracy Theories, Pseudoscience, and Human Tragedy'', an examination of [[HIV/AIDS denialism]].<ref>{{Cite journal|doi=10.1007/s12111-009-9098-1|last=Lemelle|first=Anthony|date=September 2009|title=Seth Kalichman, Denying AIDS: Conspiracy Theories, Pseudoscience, and Human Tragedy|journal=Journal of African American Studies|publisher=Springer New York|volume=13|issue=3|pages=361–364|issn=1936-4741|url=http://www.springerlink.com/content/q200136174h37253/}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|doi=10.1038/459168a|last=Moore|first=John P.|date=14 May 2009|title=The dangers of denying HIV|journal=Nature|volume=459|pages=168|url=http://www.nature.com/nature/journal/v459/n7244/full/459168a.html|issue=7244|bibcode=2009Natur.459..168M}}</ref><ref name=poz/><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://miller-mccune.com/culture_society/looking-back-in-anger-1552|title=Looking Back In Anger|last=Palmquist|first=Matt|date=3 November 2009|work=Miller-McCune|accessdate=2009-11-10|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091106082611/http://miller-mccune.com/culture_society/looking-back-in-anger-1552|archivedate=6 November 2009|df=dmy-all}}</ref> Royalties from the book fund antiretroviral drugs for people with HIV/AIDS in Africa.<ref name=poz/>
Kalichman spent a year infiltrating HIV [[denialist]] groups. He argues that denialism is often a [[coping strategy]], and that followers are often anti-government, anti-establishment, and prone to [[cognitive distortion]]s; he says that leaders in denialism exhibit [[paranoid personality disorder]].<ref name=poz/><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.newscientist.com/article/mg20627606.100-living-in-denial-why-sensible-people-reject-the-truth.html|title=Living in denial: Why sensible people reject the truth|last=MacKenzie|first=Deborah|date=19 May 2010|work=New Scientist|accessdate=17 July 2010}}</ref> He began researching denialism after reading the work of [[Nicoli Nattrass]].<ref name=poz>{{Cite news|url=http://www.poz.com/articles/seth_kalichman_aids_denialism_401_17024.shtml|title=Debunking the "Beehive" of AIDS Denialism|last=Wortman|first=James|date=3 August 2009|work=POZ|accessdate=17 July 2010}}</ref>
He is the developer of the [[Sexual Compulsivity Scale]].<ref>Seth C. Kalichman; David Rompa. [http://www.sash-list.net/kalichman-rompa-2001.pdf "The Sexual Compulsivity Scale:Further Development and Use With HIV-Positive Persons".] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120324052530/http://www.sash-list.net/kalichman-rompa-2001.pdf |date=24 March 2012 }}</ref>
